<TITLE> RAB widens hunt for Maruf Nizam </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 29 (bdnews24.com)  RAB officers raided the houses of Maruf Nizam, the prime suspect of the businessman Jamaluddin Chowdhury abduction and killing case But they failed to arrest Maruf in the raid that continued from Monday night to Tuesday. The officers of the Rapid Action Battalion said they conducted twin raids on Maruf's Chalkbazar house in the city and his village in Anwara. Maruf has been evading arrest, RAB-7 director Lt Col Hasinur Rahman told bdnews24.com. Maruf has wide corruption allegations against him. He is the younger brother of former BNP lawmaker Sarwar Jamal Nizam and navy chief Sarwar Jahan Nizam. bdnew
